{
  "texts": [
    "The data used for the present analyses were recorded during a study by Sagehorn et al. (2023) employing a standard paradigm to study face perception.",
    "In the part of the experiment relevant to this study, participants sat in front of a computer screen and passively observed pictures of either faces, blurred faces, or scrambled faces (Fig. 1).",
    "The latter two comprise the control conditions, while the former is the target.",
    "During the experiment, EEG was recorded with 128 electrodes attached according to the international 10-20 system.",
    "With the N170, the expected ERP was found using typical EEG analysis."
  ]
}